      "text": "<blockquote>Romiszowski (2004) opines that the most important learning about the implementation of edu- cational technology projects is not classroom or theory-based but gained by adopting an integrated systems approach across all project phases,and most importantly, at the full-scale implementation and management phase.He stresses that failure to do this will only result in the same“ rise and fall” trajectory as so many promising innovations in the past. (p. 5)</blockquote>\nMy problem with this argument is that it assumes a rational organisational approach that just doesn't exist. And perhaps can't exist in a complex, ever-changing environment. If you can't do this systems approach, why try?"
